Navigate to the **File Storage Config** page of the Elastic Runtime product tile.

If you want to use PCF's internal file store, select **Internal** and click **Save**.

If you want to use an external S3-compatible filestore for your Elastic
Runtime file storage, complete the following procedure:

1. Select **External S3-Compatible Filestore**.

1. Enter the **URL Endpoint** point for your filestore.

1. Enter the **Bucket Name**. If you manually configured Amazon Web Services for PCF, this will be the name that you chose in [Create S3
Buckets](./pcf-aws-component-config.html#pcfaws-s3).

1. Enter your **Access Key** and **Secret Key**. If you are using Amazon Web Services, you can retrieve your key information with the IAM credentials that you generated in [Create an IAM User for PCF](./pcf-aws-component-config.html#pcfaws-iam-user).

1. Click **Save**.

